<br>
Firebolt of Tallon was introduced as the Magician vendor-only spell. This quite simply stunned almost everyone who read up on it or saw it in action. Many mages speculated during the late phase of the beta when it was granted its godly status that it should be tuned by raising its level, perhaps swapping the spell with the less flashy but much more practical Black Steel.<br>
<br>
Data coming out on the level 61-65 Magician pets is while not as startling to Mages, is beginning to become much more mainstream. The simple fact is that the new pets are delivering damage in the 60-70 dps range, depending on circumstances. It has clearly been an across the board power boost for spelled pets, with Beastlords reporting similar if slightly less impressive results.<br>
<br>
These two points are rousing calls for nerf across class boards. Graffe's, while openly stating that the Magician bolt is a required portion of the retuning of the class, question its easy availability when compared with other nukes in their arsenal of simlilar power. Monks are outright screaming nerfs to the new pets, and you can bet that once someone does the numbers and it becomes common knowlege that Mages are rivalling Rogues now for damage there will be a melee-wide surge of resentment to these enhancements of the Magician class.<br>
<br>
I for one am tired of it. Is it the player's perception of the game's proper state that we remain it's much laughed at red-headed step child? Would it be such a travesty for Magicians to be the outright best damage dealing class, given that this damage is so riddled with issues of circumstance?<br>
<br>
After so long, mages are so hurting for numbers that it would be a very good thing for us as a class to skip just a little ahead of mudflation at the launch of this expansion. After all, you can bet your life that this (the spell lines) are pretty much it for enhancements this expansion, drops are traditionally not particularly effective for casters. I find it a point of pride that we are now being slowly reckoned as serious damage dealers rather than rod whores.<br>
<br>
Its been well over two years now since new pets entered the game. I certainly hope the developers will see the coming backlash against the new pets for what it is, a knee jerk reaction to the finalisation of a long overdue process, the restoration of the Magician class to its rightful place as a kicker of arses and a taker of names. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A> at: 11/7/02 9:31:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=salashpenumbra>Salash Penumbra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 358<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 9:36:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: It Begins</span><hr size=1> Most of PoP has yet to be revealed. Melees rely far more on equipment, and as soon as the new weapons (probably ratio 1:1 1-handers or better) start coming into the game, I'm sure we'll move back behind melee again. <p>Salash Penumbra - Summoner of Armies!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc@themagicianstower>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1224<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 10:14:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" ali