<br>
Consider that with proper buffs (Focus/Bo5/ranger atk buffs) the new water pet can reach upwards of 85 to 88dps against various level 62 mobs and lower in the planes. Also consider that with FoT + proper focus gear a mage can get near 5.0 ratio on that bolt and over 400dps. That doesn't even take into account SCF/SCM, and various other AA. Also I am hearing good things about Host of Elements as well as suspend menion. Mages recovering mana are great rates further helping with the output of damage.<br>
<br>
Most top end knights can not hit 85dps in a experience group. We have pets that are able to get near that with buffs. As I said in the other thread, these pets are very different then pets of old. They benefit greatly from stat buffs and with the new gear we can summon for them they really shine. The epic pet doesn't seem to be benefitting from all the new buffs/items like the new pets are. Today for the first time I moved Summon: Orb off my front page of my spell book. /em sheds a tear. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
